               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410510-name-706" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410510-name-706" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410510-name-706" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410510-name-706" type="given" value="MICHAEL"></interp>MICHAEL SMITH</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a linendraper, and live in Crawford-street, Marylebone. On the 24th of April, I had some shawls pinned to an iron rod at the door—I heard a noise at the door between nine and ten o'clock —I went to the door, and saw the prisoner going away—I heard a call of "Stop thief"—I ran after him, and overtook him, with one of the shawls in his possession—I called a policeman, and gave him in charge—he said he did not intend to steal it, he was only going to look at it—he was about twenty yards from the shop.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I never had the shawl at all. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> I found it in his possession.</p>
